WEBVTT

1
00:00:34.750 --> 00:00:39.667 line:82%
CHICAGO 1990.

2
00:01:43.792 --> 00:01:44.750 line:82%
That's it?

3
00:02:02.542 --> 00:02:05.208 line:82%
1st December 1990.

4
00:02:06.958 --> 00:02:12.583 line:82%
This was perhaps the most important
and dangerous day of our lives.

5
00:02:16.083 --> 00:02:19.208 line:82%
Like a boat in a storm...

6
00:02:19.500 --> 00:02:21.292 line:82%
...we were neither sinking...

7
00:02:21.750 --> 00:02:23.458 line:82%
...nor reaching the shore.

8
00:02:24.833 --> 00:02:28.292 line:82%
Today we shall look the storm
in the eye.

9
00:02:28.792 --> 00:02:30.667 line:82%
Will the storm quell...

10
00:02:31.708 --> 00:02:33.458 line:82%
...or swallow us?

11
00:02:35.250 --> 00:02:36.208 line:82%
What you got?

12
00:02:37.292 --> 00:02:38.417 line:82%
Give it here.

13
00:02:38.833 --> 00:02:41.000 line:82%
Trying to get away, kid?

14
00:02:43.000 --> 00:02:45.583 line:82%
Every storm and danger to us...

15
00:02:46.208 --> 00:02:47.625 line:82%
...was a challenge.

16
00:02:48.083 --> 00:02:48.958 line:82%
What else you got?

17
00:02:49.125 --> 00:02:50.750 line:82%
Time to amaze the world.

18
00:02:51.042 --> 00:02:53.542 line:82%
Show them an impossible feat.

19
00:02:57.000 --> 00:02:58.125 line:82%
Get him. Come on!

20
00:03:01.792 --> 00:03:03.375 line:82%
Stop! You're mine.

21
00:03:04.083 --> 00:03:05.125 line:82%
Don't let him go.

22
00:03:07.250 --> 00:03:08.417 line:82%
He's getting away.

23
00:03:38.250 --> 00:03:40.542 line:82%
THE GREAT INDIAN CIRCUS.

24
00:03:53.375 --> 00:03:55.333 line:82%
- Where is he?
- I don't know.

25
00:03:56.958 --> 00:03:58.458 line:82%
Sorry, sorry...

26
00:04:19.792 --> 00:04:20.792 line:82%
What's that?

27
00:04:21.167 --> 00:04:21.917 line:82%
Magic!

28
00:04:30.208 --> 00:04:31.583 line:82%
25$, Papa.

29
00:04:31.875 --> 00:04:34.625 line:82%
I know the bank loan is lots more.

30
00:04:37.208 --> 00:04:39.917 line:82%
Give them this.
It will help a little.

31
00:04:48.708 --> 00:04:50.958 line:82%
If I gave them your 25$...

32
00:04:52.417 --> 00:04:54.625 line:82%
...they'd be in our debt, son.

33
00:04:55.208 --> 00:04:57.917 line:82%
It's way too much.

34
00:04:58.833 --> 00:05:01.000 line:82%
As long as you have these 25$...

35
00:05:01.667 --> 00:05:04.667 line:82%
...no bank in the world can
shut our circus down.

36
00:05:07.833 --> 00:05:09.083 line:82%
But Papa...

37
00:05:09.875 --> 00:05:13.792 line:82%
...I heard you say the bank
won't listen to you.

38
00:05:14.417 --> 00:05:15.833 line:82%
But they have.

39
00:05:16.083 --> 00:05:20.542 line:82%
I said I'd put on a special show
for them.

40
00:05:21.042 --> 00:05:24.000 line:82%
"Don't shut us down if you like
the show."

41
00:05:24.375 --> 00:05:25.833 line:82%
What if they don't like it?

42
00:05:26.167 --> 00:05:27.875 line:82%
How is that possible?

43
00:05:28.958 --> 00:05:30.583 line:82%
They'll have to like it.

44
00:05:31.458 --> 00:05:33.500 line:82%
They'll have to.

45
00:05:34.375 --> 00:05:37.500 line:82%
It'll go brilliantly today.

46
00:05:38.250 --> 00:05:42.625 line:82%
Because I have a great magician
performing in my act.

47
00:05:44.292 --> 00:05:47.417 line:82%
- And who is he?
- I know.

48
00:05:48.708 --> 00:05:50.708 line:82%
Me...Sahir.

49
00:05:51.458 --> 00:05:53.833 line:82%
My name means magician.

50
00:05:56.417 --> 00:06:00.250 line:82%
Dazzle the bankers with
your magic, son.

51
00:06:01.167 --> 00:06:03.000 line:82%
You bankers...

52
00:06:07.167 --> 00:06:09.083 line:82%
WESTERN.

53
00:06:18.292 --> 00:06:20.083 line:82%
THE GREAT INDIAN CIRCUS.

54
00:06:55.333 --> 00:06:59.167 line:82%
People of God are we.
Who can defy us?

55
00:07:02.125 --> 00:07:06.000 line:82%
Basking under a thousand suns
of hope.

56
00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:09.917 line:82%
With steely resolve.

57
00:07:10.708 --> 00:07:12.250 line:82%
With fearless step.

58
00:07:12.917 --> 00:07:14.875 line:82%
Today we set forth...

59
00:07:15.708 --> 00:07:17.292 line:82%
...to write our destiny.

60
00:07:54.292 --> 00:07:55.500 line:82%
Gentlemen.

61
00:07:56.083 --> 00:08:00.000 line:82%
The Great Indian Circus.

62
00:08:46.458 --> 00:08:48.292 line:82%
And now, gentlemen.

63
00:08:49.583 --> 00:08:51.375 line:82%
My new act.

64
00:08:52.292 --> 00:08:55.958 line:82%
An act that has never been
seen before.

65
00:09:29.708 --> 00:09:30.583 line:82%
Papa...

66
00:10:35.250 --> 00:10:36.542 line:82%
The boy...

67
00:10:38.667 --> 00:10:40.125 line:82%
...in the box.

68
00:10:41.833 --> 00:10:43.333 line:82%
What do you think, Mr. Anderson?

69
00:10:57.000 --> 00:10:59.292 line:82%
You have 5 days to
hand over this place...

70
00:10:59.625 --> 00:11:01.167 line:82%
...and everything in it
we can auction.

71
00:11:06.000 --> 00:11:10.833 line:82%
I just showed you the best act
ever seen in a circus.

72
00:11:12.000 --> 00:11:13.583 line:82%
This is not a circus.

73
00:11:15.208 --> 00:11:19.417 line:82%
Circus is a woman in a short skirt
putting her head in a hippo's mouth.

74
00:11:19.750 --> 00:11:21.583 line:82%
Circus is stupid.

75
00:11:21.875 --> 00:11:23.458 line:82%
That's what people pay money for.

76
00:11:23.750 --> 00:11:26.833 line:82%
This is the future of circus,
Anderson.

77
00:11:27.292 --> 00:11:29.333 line:82%
We are bankers, Mr. Iqbal.

78
00:11:29.708 --> 00:11:32.000 line:82%
We understand the world of money.

79
00:11:32.333 --> 00:11:35.542 line:82%
You have defaulted on your payments.
You owe us.

80
00:11:35.875 --> 00:11:39.000 line:82%
This circus has not been running.

81
00:11:39.583 --> 00:11:40.833 line:82%
And it never will.

82
00:11:43.958 --> 00:11:45.083 line:82%
Please...

83
00:11:47.000 --> 00:11:48.375 line:82%
My decision is final.

84
00:12:05.875 --> 00:12:07.167 line:82%
Sir, one minute, sir.

85
00:12:08.125 --> 00:12:09.750 line:82%
Sir, please sir, don't shut us.

86
00:12:10.042 --> 00:12:12.000 line:82%
My Papa is very good.
He's the best.

87
00:12:13.875 --> 00:12:17.250 line:82%
Ours will be the best circus
in the world, sir.

88
00:12:17.625 --> 00:12:19.875 line:82%
The greatest show on earth.

89
00:12:20.333 --> 00:12:21.667 line:82%
Sir...

90
00:12:24.292 --> 00:12:25.250 line:82%
Sir...

91
00:12:27.000 --> 00:12:31.083 line:82%
Sir, we'll rouse the sleeping.
Look!

92
00:12:32.875 --> 00:12:35.208 line:82%
Make the sad laugh.

93
00:12:36.583 --> 00:12:40.667 line:82%
We'll show the world
feats never seen before.

94
00:12:41.750 --> 00:12:44.583 line:82%
No one can match us, sir.

95
00:12:48.500 --> 00:12:49.667 line:82%
Sir...

96
00:12:54.667 --> 00:12:55.375 line:82%
Please...

97
00:12:57.042 --> 00:12:58.542 line:82%
Please, please.

98
00:12:58.958 --> 00:12:59.875 line:82%
I beg you.

99
00:13:00.292 --> 00:13:01.333 line:82%
Give us one chance.

100
00:13:01.708 --> 00:13:02.542 line:82%
Sahir!

101
00:13:04.708 --> 00:13:05.625 line:82%
No.

102
00:13:07.000 --> 00:13:08.250 line:82%
You must never beg.

103
00:13:10.000 --> 00:13:11.542 line:82%
Preserving our honour...

104
00:13:12.542 --> 00:13:14.292 line:82%
...is in our hands, always.

105
00:13:18.250 --> 00:13:21.375 line:82%
This circus is my life.
You're tearing it from me.

106
00:13:22.583 --> 00:13:24.208 line:82%
Tearing it from me.

107
00:13:34.292 --> 00:13:35.958 line:82%
Don't try and threaten me.

108
00:13:48.125 --> 00:13:49.125 line:82%
You bankers...

109
00:13:53.417 --> 00:13:55.917 line:82%
May you rot in hell!

110
00:13:56.583 --> 00:13:57.917 line:82%
Papa...

111
00:14:43.042 --> 00:14:48.000 line:82%
People of God are we.
Who can defy us?

112
00:14:50.917 --> 00:14:55.167 line:82%
Basking under a thousand suns
of hope.

113
00:14:57.167 --> 00:14:59.000 line:82%
With steely resolve.

114
00:14:59.708 --> 00:15:01.667 line:82%
With fearless step.

115
00:15:02.333 --> 00:15:04.708 line:82%
Today we set forth...

116
00:15:05.250 --> 00:15:06.625 line:82%
...to write our destiny.

117
00:15:27.292 --> 00:15:30.833 line:82%
WESTERN BANK OF CHICAGO.

118
00:15:32.417 --> 00:15:34.750 line:82%
Help. I'm homeless.

119
00:15:35.958 --> 00:15:38.833 line:82%
Won't somebody please help?

120
00:20:54.792 --> 00:20:56.708 line:82%
The suspect is trapped in the garage.

121
00:20:57.000 --> 00:20:58.667 line:82%
I want a perimeter around
this building.

122
00:20:59.000 --> 00:21:01.000 line:82%
He's in the basement.
He can't run anywhere.

123
00:21:01.292 --> 00:21:02.208 line:82%
We've got him.

124
00:21:36.583 --> 00:21:38.583 line:82%
Captain, you're never
going to believe this one.

125
00:21:38.917 --> 00:21:40.625 line:82%
He went in there,
came out somewhere else.

126
00:21:40.958 --> 00:21:42.375 line:82%
How does he do it?

127
00:22:02.292 --> 00:22:05.875 line:82%
We have lost visual on the suspect.

128
00:22:06.083 --> 00:22:08.750 line:82%
I repeat we have lost visual contact.

129
00:22:10.875 --> 00:22:15.042 line:82%
YASH RAJ FILMS
PRESENTS.

130
00:25:12.792 --> 00:25:17.250 line:82%
DHOOM 3.

131
00:25:33.208 --> 00:25:34.667 line:82%
Where is Jai?

132
00:25:35.000 --> 00:25:35.542 line:82%
Means?

133
00:25:35.750 --> 00:25:37.792 line:82%
Is Jai showing up?

134
00:25:38.667 --> 00:25:40.083 line:82%
He's not taking my calls.

135
00:25:48.208 --> 00:25:50.750 line:82%
Non-stick pans. Pressure cookers
on sale.

136
00:25:51.250 --> 00:25:53.833 line:82%
Buy them for your missus?
Damn good deal, boss.

137
00:26:05.375 --> 00:26:06.667 line:82%
You'll shoot me?

138
00:26:07.167 --> 00:26:07.625 line:82%
Yes.

139
00:26:09.208 --> 00:26:12.458 line:82%
Look at my face. Take your time.

140
00:26:13.292 --> 00:26:14.417 line:82%
Short version?

141
00:26:14.958 --> 00:26:16.708 line:82%
Star material, no?

142
00:26:18.042 --> 00:26:21.417 line:82%
With a great face like mine,
I end up in the police force.

143
00:26:21.833 --> 00:26:24.292 line:82%
And you'll blow me away?
For free?

144
00:26:25.583 --> 00:26:26.917 line:82%
Your hands will tremble.

145
00:26:27.375 --> 00:26:30.458 line:82%
Your gun will see me and say:
"Wow! Handsome guy.

146
00:26:30.792 --> 00:26:31.917 line:82%
"Let him go."

147
00:26:32.458 --> 00:26:34.958 line:82%
Forget what I say.
Listen to your gun, brother.

148
00:26:35.333 --> 00:26:38.375 line:82%
So you figured you'd just
stroll in here...

149
00:26:39.083 --> 00:26:40.458 line:82%
...and arrest me?

150
00:26:41.958 --> 00:26:44.583 line:82%
And I'd go with you to jail,
all meek?

151
00:26:46.875 --> 00:26:48.458 line:82%
Why think that?

152
00:26:52.000 --> 00:26:53.292 line:82%
- Truth?
- Please.

153
00:26:55.708 --> 00:27:00.667 line:82%
On 15 August, Independence Day,
we all take an oath.

154
00:27:01.125 --> 00:27:02.708 line:82%
That India is free.

155
00:27:03.417 --> 00:27:07.417 line:82%
And all Indians are equal.
I take the oath, too.

156
00:27:08.167 --> 00:27:10.000 line:82%
But I've got this nagging doubt.

157
00:27:10.208 --> 00:27:11.625 line:82%
Everyone equal? Means what?

158
00:27:11.917 --> 00:27:13.375 line:82%
You and me? Equal?

159
00:27:13.792 --> 00:27:16.375 line:82%
Aunty next door and the star
Hema Malini, equal?

160
00:27:20.333 --> 00:27:21.083 line:82%
No, boss.

161
00:27:22.000 --> 00:27:23.000 line:82%
Something fishy.

162
00:27:24.000 --> 00:27:24.833 line:82%
Hot air!

163
00:27:26.542 --> 00:27:27.292 line:82%
You stand here...

164
00:27:27.667 --> 00:27:28.625 line:82%
...in your shiny suit.

165
00:27:28.917 --> 00:27:33.042 line:82%
While poor Raju there can't even
afford plastic rain cover.

166
00:27:36.000 --> 00:27:38.750 line:82%
How come? Sure, India is free.

167
00:27:39.292 --> 00:27:40.875 line:82%
But people like you enslave her.

168
00:27:41.333 --> 00:27:42.792 line:82%
Made two Indias.

169
00:27:43.750 --> 00:27:45.000 line:82%
One for us punters.

170
00:27:45.250 --> 00:27:46.667 line:82%
One for you big shots.

171
00:27:47.000 --> 00:27:48.000 line:82%
Whose horse wins?

172
00:27:48.250 --> 00:27:50.833 line:82%
Who wins the match?
Who wins the elections?

173
00:27:51.250 --> 00:27:52.833 line:82%
The answers are in your pocket.

174
00:27:53.083 --> 00:27:54.333 line:82%
I want that pocket.

175
00:27:54.708 --> 00:27:56.792 line:82%
And the scum that live in it.

176
00:27:57.083 --> 00:27:58.708 line:82%
I'll wring their necks.

177
00:27:59.042 --> 00:28:01.875 line:82%
The day your sort is rotting
in jail...

178
00:28:02.083 --> 00:28:04.083 line:82%
...that day India will be truly free.

179
00:28:11.417 --> 00:28:13.292 line:82%
All your noble thoughts?

180
00:28:15.042 --> 00:28:17.375 line:82%
Actually, all Jai's ideas.

181
00:28:17.875 --> 00:28:20.208 line:82%
Gave you the short version.
You see...

182
00:28:21.708 --> 00:28:25.542 line:82%
I arrest guys. But Jai's fists
do the talking.

183
00:28:26.375 --> 00:28:28.375 line:82%
Makes pulp out of guys.

184
00:28:29.125 --> 00:28:30.542 line:82%
Tried aunty's chutney?

185
00:28:31.000 --> 00:28:32.000 line:82%
That smooth.

186
00:28:32.292 --> 00:28:35.000 line:82%
So he'll come with an army
to save your face?

187
00:28:35.208 --> 00:28:38.750 line:82%
An army? One Jai is all I need.

188
00:28:39.250 --> 00:28:42.625 line:82%
But no one makes an entry
quite like him.

189
00:28:43.542 --> 00:28:47.125 line:82%
And that brain of his?
No one can match him.

190
00:28:48.000 --> 00:28:50.625 line:82%
You're not going to believe...

191
00:28:51.167 --> 00:28:53.583 line:82%
...what he'll do to you.

192
00:29:07.125 --> 00:29:08.375 line:82%
Solid entry, brother.

193
00:29:17.042 --> 00:29:18.042 line:82%
What the hell?

194
00:29:32.833 --> 00:29:33.750 line:82%
Rot in jail!

195
00:29:34.000 --> 00:29:34.500 line:82%
Ali!

196
00:31:22.583 --> 00:31:24.167 line:82%
Hey! They keep coming.

197
00:31:28.125 --> 00:31:29.250 line:82%
Grind those brakes!

198
00:31:29.833 --> 00:31:33.000 line:82%
- They aren't working
- Mummy, help!

199
00:31:51.792 --> 00:31:52.917 line:82%
- Ali.
- Yes.

200
00:31:54.042 --> 00:31:55.083 line:82%
Run!

201
00:34:53.333 --> 00:34:54.042 line:82%
Excuse me, ma'am.

202
00:34:54.250 --> 00:34:56.167 line:82%
Ma'am, what can you tell us
about the robbery?

203
00:34:56.750 --> 00:34:59.333 line:82%
A bank robbery in this
day and age?

204
00:35:14.917 --> 00:35:16.042 line:82%
Mr. Anderson.

205
00:35:19.625 --> 00:35:21.208 line:82%
Who's this guy robbing us?

206
00:35:21.458 --> 00:35:24.542 line:82%
It's a thief, sir.
That's all I can say now.

207
00:35:25.250 --> 00:35:26.583 line:82%
I mean this.

208
00:35:27.292 --> 00:35:29.000 line:82%
"Bankers! May you rot in hell!"

209
00:35:29.250 --> 00:35:32.625 line:82%
This is the second robbery at one
of our branches in a year.

210
00:35:33.083 --> 00:35:35.333 line:82%
First the Wacker Street branch
and now this.

211
00:35:35.750 --> 00:35:39.292 line:82%
He takes the money and what he can't
take he destroys.

212
00:35:40.250 --> 00:35:42.958 line:82%
My bank is going down
and I don't like it.

213
00:35:46.292 --> 00:35:47.792 line:82%
THE GREAT INDIAN CIRCUS.

214
00:35:57.792 --> 00:35:58.333 line:82%
25$.

215
00:35:59.042 --> 00:36:01.375 line:82%
I know the bank loan is lots more.

216
00:36:01.750 --> 00:36:03.333 line:82%
As long as you have these 25$...

217
00:36:03.833 --> 00:36:06.250 line:82%
...no bank in the world can
shut our circus down.

218
00:36:07.000 --> 00:36:09.333 line:82%
This circus has not been running
and it never will.

219
00:36:09.875 --> 00:36:12.042 line:82%
Ours will be the best circus
in the world.

220
00:36:12.375 --> 00:36:14.375 line:82%
- The greatest show on earth.
- This is not a circus.

221
00:36:14.708 --> 00:36:17.333 line:82%
This the future of circus, Anderson.

222
00:36:17.917 --> 00:36:22.125 line:82%
This circus is my life.
You're tearing it away from me.

223
00:36:38.833 --> 00:36:40.292 line:82%
My Papa is very good.

224
00:36:41.250 --> 00:36:42.542 line:82%
He's the best.

225
00:37:28.833 --> 00:37:30.708 line:82%
THE GREAT INDIAN CIRCUS.

226
00:37:38.458 --> 00:37:40.417 line:82%
I've come home, Papa.

227
00:37:43.042 --> 00:37:44.500 line:82%
I've come home.

228
00:38:18.750 --> 00:38:21.542 line:82%
Ali, this is a new city.
Let's see a new you.

229
00:38:21.958 --> 00:38:26.083 line:82%
Eyes to yourself. No girl here
is going to fall for you.

230
00:38:26.458 --> 00:38:29.000 line:82%
Ali is an international cop now.

231
00:38:29.333 --> 00:38:32.792 line:82%
Means...Ali's eyes are glued tight
on thieves.

232
00:38:33.292 --> 00:38:36.125 line:82%
And Ali's ears...

233
00:38:37.167 --> 00:38:37.875 line:82%
What?

234
00:38:38.250 --> 00:38:40.833 line:82%
I can tell. A four-cylinder.

235
00:38:42.250 --> 00:38:47.750 line:82%
Fabulous compression! It's a BMW.

236
00:39:32.333 --> 00:39:34.458 line:82%
I am officer Victoria Williams.

237
00:39:34.750 --> 00:39:36.833 line:82%
Chicago Police Department,
Intelligence Wing.

238
00:39:37.083 --> 00:39:40.333 line:82%
We've met before. London?
