Thief, thief! Stop!
Stop that thief.

950
01:52:30.250 --> 01:52:31.958 line:82%
Hey you Indian, come back.

951
01:52:32.250 --> 01:52:33.958 line:82%
I'll kill you.

952
01:52:37.083 --> 01:52:38.333 line:82%
I'll kill you.

953
01:52:39.917 --> 01:52:40.958 line:82%
Excuse me, please.

954
01:52:41.167 --> 01:52:44.042 line:82%
You see Indian thief? Tall chap?
This much, you see him?

955
01:52:44.375 --> 01:52:46.208 line:82%
I kill him with this.

956
01:52:47.083 --> 01:52:47.792 line:82%
Thank you.

957
01:52:48.000 --> 01:52:50.125 line:82%
I kill you, I kill you.

958
01:52:53.208 --> 01:52:57.833 line:82%
I no kill you. I kill Indian. Coming,
taking your phone number.

959
01:52:58.083 --> 01:52:59.208 line:82%
Thank you.

960
01:53:05.000 --> 01:53:06.625 line:82%
Stealing? Very bad.

961
01:53:12.875 --> 01:53:14.167 line:82%
I'm not a thief.

962
01:53:15.917 --> 01:53:19.458 line:82%
If you don't eat for 4 days, your
sense of morality vanishes.

963
01:53:22.667 --> 01:53:25.708 line:82%
Happy Burger! Makes you happy
if you eat it.

964
01:53:39.917 --> 01:53:41.917 line:82%
Know who the real big thieves are?

965
01:53:43.417 --> 01:53:44.417 line:82%
The banks.

966
01:53:47.208 --> 01:53:49.917 line:82%
They can ruin a man in a matter
of days.

967
01:53:50.958 --> 01:53:52.708 line:82%
Everyone steals.

968
01:53:54.167 --> 01:53:56.833 line:82%
But you must find something
worth stealing.

969
01:53:57.542 --> 01:53:58.625 line:82%
What do you steal?

970
01:54:06.625 --> 01:54:07.583 line:82%
Fun!

971
01:54:56.625 --> 01:54:58.750 line:82%
Terrific ride. But there's one
even better.

972
01:54:59.042 --> 01:55:01.000 line:82%
- Which one?
- Raging Bull.

973
01:55:02.000 --> 01:55:03.000 line:82%
Let's go.

974
01:55:07.917 --> 01:55:08.917 line:82%
Where are you going?

975
01:55:09.167 --> 01:55:11.958 line:82%
I come here every Sunday
from 11.45 to 3.

976
01:55:12.625 --> 01:55:14.542 line:82%
Can't miss the bus home.

977
01:55:18.583 --> 01:55:22.042 line:82%
See you next Sunday? Same time?
We'll steal some fun.

978
01:55:24.208 --> 01:55:26.500 line:82%
The Great Indian Circus.
Great fun.

979
01:55:29.417 --> 01:55:30.542 line:82%
Thanks, my friend.

980
01:55:33.208 --> 01:55:35.958 line:82%
I've never had any friends.

981
01:55:36.958 --> 01:55:38.625 line:82%
Neither have I.

982
01:55:39.958 --> 01:55:40.792 line:82%
Good.

983
01:55:42.708 --> 01:55:43.500 line:82%
Good.

984
01:55:48.167 --> 01:55:49.000 line:82%
See you.

985
01:55:54.042 --> 01:55:57.083 line:82%
Papa, I thought I didn't know
how to make friends.

986
01:55:57.542 --> 01:56:02.875 line:82%
But friendship isn't maths.
No rules like maths.

987
01:56:04.000 --> 01:56:05.417 line:82%
My first friend.

988
01:56:05.833 --> 01:56:09.208 line:82%
I felt like telling Sahir.
But he won't like it.

989
01:56:10.083 --> 01:56:12.417 line:82%
He has no time for friendship.

990
01:56:13.750 --> 01:56:15.917 line:82%
Some things are best left a secret.

991
01:56:17.125 --> 01:56:19.583 line:82%
I have two secrets now.

992
01:56:20.958 --> 01:56:22.042 line:82%
Aliya.

993
01:56:22.542 --> 01:56:23.833 line:82%
And my friend.

994
01:56:24.458 --> 01:56:26.167 line:82%
FRIEND.

995
01:56:39.083 --> 01:56:42.583 line:82%
That's real brains.
Brains in Hindi is...?

996
01:56:43.708 --> 01:56:44.583 line:82%
That's real brains.

997
01:56:46.500 --> 01:56:48.542 line:82%
God gave me movie star looks.

998
01:56:48.875 --> 01:56:52.458 line:82%
And gave Jai brains as sharp
as Karim's razor.

999
01:56:53.125 --> 01:56:56.458 line:82%
Karim? Who? He bleaches
my face, cuts my hair.

1000
01:56:57.542 --> 01:56:59.750 line:82%
You think she's researching
your life?

1001
01:57:00.125 --> 01:57:02.167 line:82%
I'm researching hers.

1002
01:57:02.542 --> 01:57:05.958 line:82%
I have her horoscope. Native place,
beauty parlour, the lot.

1003
01:57:06.375 --> 01:57:10.250 line:82%
You're here to catch a thief.
Do your job. Got it?

1004
01:57:11.417 --> 01:57:14.875 line:82%
This is the list of things
I need to know.

1005
01:57:15.125 --> 01:57:16.792 line:82%
Sahir and the Great Indian Circus.

1006
01:57:17.042 --> 01:57:18.542 line:82%
Think you can find out for me?

1007
01:57:18.958 --> 01:57:19.833 line:82%
I'll get on it.

1008
01:57:20.083 --> 01:57:21.792 line:82%
How will his history help us?

1009
01:57:22.042 --> 01:57:25.625 line:82%
Because it'll tell us what
Sahir plans to do next.

1010
01:57:26.042 --> 01:57:29.458 line:82%
You really won't get it.
So don't act like you do.

1011
01:57:29.958 --> 01:57:31.375 line:82%
Shall I act like she's my date?

1012
01:57:31.833 --> 01:57:34.708 line:82%
Focus on your work.
Not on the Kamasutra.

1013
01:57:59.500 --> 01:58:03.250 line:82%
- Mr.Iqbal Khan, how are you?
- I'm fine, Jennifer.

1014
01:58:03.750 --> 01:58:04.750 line:82%
My locker, please.

1015
01:58:05.375 --> 01:58:07.583 line:82%
I've been well. Just my knees,
you know.

1016
01:58:08.083 --> 01:58:10.000 line:82%
This weekend my boyfriend
was playing basketball...

1017
01:58:29.917 --> 01:58:34.667 line:82%
This is for you. Here.

1018
01:58:35.083 --> 01:58:37.375 line:82%
Thank you. See you in a minute.

1019
01:59:01.083 --> 01:59:05.417 line:82%
Papa, you said as long as
I have these 25$...

1020
01:59:06.167 --> 01:59:10.083 line:82%
...no bank in the world can
shut our circus down.

1021
01:59:13.958 --> 01:59:16.125 line:82%
This is the bank's last day, Papa.

1022
01:59:19.458 --> 01:59:21.042 line:82%
The bank is about to close.

1023
01:59:23.208 --> 01:59:24.500 line:82%
Forever.

1024
01:59:55.958 --> 01:59:58.500 line:82%
Adding two and two? Eh?

1025
02:00:00.000 --> 02:00:01.417 line:82%
Tomorrow you'll see four.

1026
02:00:11.042 --> 02:00:12.625 line:82%
His Highness the Great.

1027
02:00:14.000 --> 02:00:15.250 line:82%
The burger thief?

1028
02:00:15.833 --> 02:00:18.583 line:82%
I found myself a job.
Today it's my treat.

1029
02:00:19.875 --> 02:00:21.375 line:82%
I saw your circus act.

1030
02:00:21.625 --> 02:00:22.792 line:82%
Too good.

1031
02:00:23.083 --> 02:00:25.667 line:82%
I want your autograph.
And a photograph.

1032
02:00:27.000 --> 02:00:29.458 line:82%
I clapped like crazy at the end.
But you didn't see me.

1033
02:00:30.000 --> 02:00:33.000 line:82%
Forget me. You didn't even notice
your girlfriend Aliya.

1034
02:00:33.458 --> 02:00:35.042 line:82%
The Wonder Girl.

1035
02:00:36.958 --> 02:00:38.917 line:82%
She isn't my GF.

1036
02:00:39.875 --> 02:00:41.792 line:82%
Aliya isn't your GF?

1037
02:00:43.250 --> 02:00:44.417 line:82%
Why not?

1038
02:00:45.167 --> 02:00:47.875 line:82%
What makes you think
she's my girlfriend?

1039
02:00:49.000 --> 02:00:50.708 line:82%
I have very sharp eyes.

1040
02:00:51.125 --> 02:00:53.375 line:82%
I read minds at a glance.

1041
02:00:53.792 --> 02:00:58.417 line:82%
The way she looked at you only
a GF looks at her BF like that.

1042
02:00:59.167 --> 02:01:01.167 line:82%
Thought she'd kiss you.

1043
02:01:02.042 --> 02:01:03.417 line:82%
She's not that kind.

1044
02:01:05.083 --> 02:01:06.792 line:82%
You know nothing.

1045
02:01:07.167 --> 02:01:08.167 line:82%
Stupid.

1046
02:01:34.333 --> 02:01:37.833 line:82%
- Makes you happy...
- I know.

1047
02:01:46.250 --> 02:01:48.500 line:82%
I love her.

1048
02:01:53.167 --> 02:01:54.833 line:82%
So? I was spot on.

1049
02:01:55.917 --> 02:01:58.167 line:82%
But she isn't my GF.

1050
02:01:59.917 --> 02:02:03.375 line:82%
She doesn't even know
that I like her.

1051
02:02:04.875 --> 02:02:06.875 line:82%
Impossible, my friend.

1052
02:02:09.417 --> 02:02:12.000 line:82%
When you stand near her
and hold her hand...

1053
02:02:12.292 --> 02:02:14.000 line:82%
Know how she looks at you?

1054
02:02:14.208 --> 02:02:17.708 line:82%
The way Laila looks at her
beloved Majnu.

1055
02:02:19.000 --> 02:02:21.083 line:82%
When you dance with her...

1056
02:02:21.417 --> 02:02:22.875 line:82%
...she looks at you the way...

1057
02:02:23.167 --> 02:02:24.958 line:82%
...Angelina looks at Brad.

1058
02:02:26.250 --> 02:02:28.583 line:82%
When she stands close to you...

1059
02:02:29.542 --> 02:02:30.917 line:82%
...know how she looks?

1060
02:02:31.250 --> 02:02:32.708 line:82%
The way Aliya looks at Sahir.

1061
02:02:33.750 --> 02:02:34.625 line:82%
Yes!

1062
02:02:35.292 --> 02:02:38.042 line:82%
She sees no one but Sahir.

1063
02:02:42.875 --> 02:02:44.458 line:82%
She looks the way...

1064
02:02:45.167 --> 02:02:47.792 line:82%
...Aliya looks at Sahir.

1065
02:02:48.458 --> 02:02:50.375 line:82%
See? I knew it.

1066
02:02:51.708 --> 02:02:54.208 line:82%
Sees no one but Sahir.

1067
02:02:55.750 --> 02:02:58.167 line:82%
The way Aliya looks at Sahir...

1068
02:03:00.125 --> 02:03:06.375 line:82%
But Samar sees only Aliya.

1069
02:03:33.208 --> 02:03:36.833 line:82%
I'm doing your act today.

1070
02:03:37.917 --> 02:03:41.125 line:82%
You will take my place
and I'll take yours.

1071
02:03:41.792 --> 02:03:43.292 line:82%
Are you crazy?

1072
02:03:43.708 --> 02:03:45.750 line:82%
Want the circus to close down?

1073
02:03:46.792 --> 02:03:48.000 line:82%
Why say that?

1074
02:03:48.625 --> 02:03:50.375 line:82%
Why? Don't you know why?

1075
02:03:50.667 --> 02:03:53.750 line:82%
That's our trick. The world sees one,
but we're two.

1076
02:03:54.208 --> 02:03:57.500 line:82%
As if anyone would find out.

1077
02:03:59.000 --> 02:03:59.875 line:82%
No.

1078
02:04:01.042 --> 02:04:02.500 line:82%
I'm doing it.

1079
02:04:03.167 --> 02:04:05.167 line:82%
You can't. We haven't rehearsed.

1080
02:04:05.583 --> 02:04:07.458 line:82%
Don't need to.

1081
02:04:09.083 --> 02:04:12.792 line:82%
I'm always Sahir. Today see what
being Samar is like.

1082
02:04:13.917 --> 02:04:16.625 line:82%
- Stop it! You can't do it.
- Sure I can.

1083
02:04:17.792 --> 02:04:19.542 line:82%
We swap places today.

1084
02:04:26.542 --> 02:04:28.500 line:82%
5 minutes. And you're on.

1085
02:04:34.417 --> 02:04:35.458 line:82%
All right.

1086
02:04:36.500 --> 02:04:37.583 line:82%
You're Sahir today.

1087
02:04:39.208 --> 02:04:40.125 line:82%
I'm Samar.

1088
02:04:42.625 --> 02:04:43.792 line:82%
For the first...

1089
02:04:44.583 --> 02:04:45.583 line:82%
...and the last time.

1090
02:05:02.917 --> 02:05:06.000 line:82%
People of God are we.
Who can defy us?

1091
02:05:06.250 --> 02:05:08.708 line:82%
I'd never forget Papa's words.
No need reminding me.

1092
02:06:52.708 --> 02:06:54.292 line:82%
You're totally crazy, boss.

1093
02:06:54.875 --> 02:06:56.125 line:82%
Always have been.

1094
02:07:12.583 --> 02:07:14.667 line:82%
I thought it was just me.

1095
02:07:15.167 --> 02:07:17.542 line:82%
But I think you were flirting too.

1096
02:07:19.375 --> 02:07:21.167 line:82%
I love this "flirting" term.

1097
02:07:21.625 --> 02:07:26.875 line:82%
Something happened today.
No! A lot happened.

1098
02:07:27.708 --> 02:07:31.375 line:82%
Something electric flowed
between us.

1099
02:07:36.833 --> 02:07:38.500 line:82%
I can still feel it.

1100
02:07:40.250 --> 02:07:41.208 line:82%
Well?

1101
02:07:43.292 --> 02:07:45.417 line:82%
What do we do about
this electricity?

1102
02:07:46.667 --> 02:07:47.708 line:82%
What do we do?

1103
02:07:48.125 --> 02:07:52.458 line:82%
When some things happen in life,
you can't let them pass.

1104
02:07:53.125 --> 02:07:56.292 line:82%
Everything has its moment.
It's all timing.

1105
02:07:57.000 --> 02:07:58.292 line:82%
One second late.

1106
02:07:58.917 --> 02:08:00.083 line:82%
It's all over.

1107
02:08:01.625 --> 02:08:02.875 line:82%
If I walk away, all shy.

1108
02:08:03.125 --> 02:08:06.167 line:82%
A year later, I'm throwing petals
on your wedding day.

1109
02:08:07.167 --> 02:08:10.167 line:82%
Blaming my bad luck. If only I had
spoken out.

1110
02:08:10.625 --> 02:08:14.125 line:82%
If only I had said something.
If only, if only.

1111
02:08:14.833 --> 02:08:18.042 line:82%
I'm not an "if only" person.

1112
02:08:21.875 --> 02:08:22.875 line:82%
How about a date?

1113
02:08:24.000 --> 02:08:25.958 line:82%
- You and me.
- OK.

1114
02:08:30.708 --> 02:08:31.875 line:82%
- Ten minutes?
- OK.

1115
02:08:32.083 --> 02:08:33.292 line:82%
At the gate.

1116
02:08:59.083 --> 02:09:00.792 line:82%
Going somewhere?

1117
02:09:01.875 --> 02:09:03.542 line:82%
It's not Sunday.

1118
02:09:05.083 --> 02:09:06.875 line:82%
I have a date.

1119
02:09:08.292 --> 02:09:09.583 line:82%
With Aliya.

1120
02:09:14.917 --> 02:09:15.833 line:82%
Aliya.

1121
02:09:20.042 --> 02:09:22.917 line:82%
So you like her?

1122
02:09:24.833 --> 02:09:26.833 line:82%
Does she like you?

1123
02:09:29.625 --> 02:09:31.833 line:82%
But who does she really like?

1124
02:09:33.125 --> 02:09:37.458 line:82%
- Me, of course
- Yes? Like all the others...

1125
02:09:38.625 --> 02:09:40.792 line:82%
...she knows only me.

1126
02:09:41.500 --> 02:09:45.250 line:82%
- Why didn't she speak before?
- Never gave her the chance.

1127
02:09:49.083 --> 02:09:51.917 line:82%
We're this close to our goal.
This close.

1128
02:09:52.667 --> 02:09:55.583 line:82%
We're winning, the bank's losing
because we're two.

1129
02:09:56.458 --> 02:09:58.042 line:82%
Papa's secret.

1130
02:09:58.833 --> 02:10:01.000 line:82%
Our lives have a purpose.

1131
02:10:01.542 --> 02:10:05.917 line:82%
So don't do anything to
threaten that purpose.

1132
02:10:11.583 --> 02:10:14.667 line:82%
She'll feel bad if I don't show up.

1133
02:10:16.250 --> 02:10:17.750 line:82%
I'll feel bad too.

1134
02:10:19.083 --> 02:10:21.125 line:82%
It's just one evening.

1135
02:10:21.583 --> 02:10:23.167 line:82%
I'm not a kid anymore.

1136
02:10:27.167 --> 02:10:28.750 line:82%
What did you imagine?

1137
02:10:29.583 --> 02:10:32.000 line:82%
You see her and she'll fall
head over heels for you?

1138
02:10:33.125 --> 02:10:34.000 line:82%
How?

1139
02:10:34.542 --> 02:10:37.000 line:82%
How will you talk to her?
Stammer away?

1140
02:10:37.458 --> 02:10:39.875 line:82%
You'll get all tongue-tied.

1141
02:10:41.625 --> 02:10:44.250 line:82%
You're a secret. Hidden in
that box for good reason.

1142
02:10:44.667 --> 02:10:46.625 line:82%
Because you're weak.

1143
02:10:50.000 --> 02:10:53.000 line:82%
We've always protected you.
First Papa. Then me.

1144
02:10:53.917 --> 02:10:58.000 line:82%
Never faced the world. That's
why you're inside and I'm out.

1145
02:10:58.500 --> 02:11:01.625 line:82%
On the stage we can pass as one.
Not in the real world.

1146
02:11:03.292 --> 02:11:07.083 line:82%
In two minutes, she'll realise
you're not Sahir.

1147
02:11:08.292 --> 02:11:12.208 line:82%
Stick that in your skull
till it totally sinks in.

1148
02:11:14.208 --> 02:11:17.250 line:82%
You're my shadow. Stay that way.
You bloody idiot.

1149
02:11:30.542 --> 02:11:32.125 line:82%
I'm not a shadow.

1150
02:11:32.625 --> 02:11:34.000 line:82%
I'm Samar.

1151
02:11:38.917 --> 02:11:41.708 line:82%
I'm not weak. I'm Samar.

1152
02:11:45.083 --> 02:11:46.833 line:82%
Papa's two hands.

1153
02:11:47.208 --> 02:11:48.875 line:82%
Sahir and Samar.

1154
02:11:50.458 --> 02:11:53.625 line:82%
You get all the praise for my act.

1155
02:11:54.708 --> 02:11:56.875 line:82%
My ideas. Applause for you.

1156
02:11:57.208 --> 02:12:00.667 line:82%
Now you're the mastermind
and I'm the threat?

1157
02:12:05.667 --> 02:12:08.417 line:82%
We have the same face.
But we have two minds.

1158
02:12:08.958 --> 02:12:10.250 line:82%
Two hearts.

1159
02:12:12.292 --> 02:12:15.083 line:82%
You want me to obey your
every command.

1160
02:12:16.125 --> 02:12:20.250 line:82%
I must want what you want.
Feel what you feel. Why?

1161
02:12:21.250 --> 02:12:22.417 line:82%
Why always me?

1162
02:12:25.375 --> 02:12:28.250 line:82%
You be my shadow. Rot in that box.
You're weak.

1163
02:13:35.917 --> 02:13:38.000 line:82%
Sorry. Date cancelled.

1164
02:13:41.417 --> 02:13:42.000 line:82%
Why?

1165
02:13:42.708 --> 02:13:44.917 line:82%
Don't date boys with untied
shoelaces.

1166
02:13:49.917 --> 02:13:50.708 line:82%
Come on.

1167
02:13:52.167 --> 02:13:53.917 line:82%
What if I told you...

1168
02:13:54.750 --> 02:13:56.583 line:82%
...I don't know how to tie them.

1169
02:13:57.792 --> 02:13:59.250 line:82%
Sweet trick!

1170
02:13:59.917 --> 02:14:02.750 line:82%
Girl at your feet on the very
first date.

1171
02:14:03.792 --> 02:14:05.167 line:82%
I like it.

1172
02:14:06.250 --> 02:14:07.167 line:82%
Albert Einstein.

1173
02:14:08.833 --> 02:14:10.792 line:82%
He couldn't tie his shoelaces either.

1174
02:14:11.417 --> 02:14:12.167 line:82%
It's a fact.

1175
02:14:13.333 --> 02:14:16.042 line:82%
Mr. Einstein of the circus.

1176
02:14:16.875 --> 02:14:19.042 line:82%
The man who knows every trick
in the book.

1177
02:14:20.000 --> 02:14:21.042 line:82%
Except this.

1178
02:14:23.125 --> 02:14:24.875 line:82%
It's kind of cute.

1179
02:14:25.917 --> 02:14:27.292 line:82%
Almost sexy.

1180
02:14:36.583 --> 02:14:38.458 line:82%
I can't brush my teeth with
my right hand.

1181
02:14:38.792 --> 02:14:39.792 line:82%
So what am I?

1182
02:14:45.167 --> 02:14:46.125 line:82%
What is it?

1183
02:14:48.500 --> 02:14:49.375 line:82%
Electricity.

1184
02:14:52.583 --> 02:14:55.125 line:82%
- So where are we going?
- I don't know.

1185
02:14:57.042 --> 02:15:01.750 line:82%
A dead ringer just walked by
with a sexy babe in tow.

1186
02:15:02.083 --> 02:15:02.875 line:82%
Follow them.

1187
02:15:03.125 --> 02:15:04.667 line:82%
Roger. Over and out.

1188
02:15:05.000 --> 02:15:06.000 line:82%
What?

1189
02:15:06.500 --> 02:15:08.667 line:82%
Since I got here...

1190
02:15:08.958 --> 02:15:11.208 line:82%
I've been dying to say:
"Over and out."

1191
02:15:11.583 --> 02:15:13.417 line:82%
Never had the chance.

1192
02:15:14.042 --> 02:15:15.250 line:82%
- Ali.
- Yes.

1193
02:15:15.708 --> 02:15:16.375 line:82%
Buzz off!

1194
02:15:16.750 --> 02:15:19.250 line:82%
Buzzing off. Let's buzz.

1195
02:15:20.583 --> 02:15:21.417 line:82%
Gentlemen.

1196
02:15:21.875 --> 02:15:24.708 line:82%
Thank you for coming at short notice
for this emergency meeting.

1197
02:15:25.542 --> 02:15:27.750 line:82%
Whatever it is, it had better be good.

1198
02:15:28.083 --> 02:15:30.167 line:82%
I don't have much time.
Time is money.

1199
02:15:30.625 --> 02:15:33.208 line:82%
Absolutely right, Mr. Anderson.
You don't have much time.

1200
02:15:33.750 --> 02:15:36.667 line:82%
And if you don't be quiet, soon you
won't have any money either.

1201
02:15:39.417 --> 02:15:42.708 line:82%
The Western Bank of Chicago
is being robbed for a reason.

1202
02:15:43.208 --> 02:15:45.250 line:82%
That reason is the Great
Indian Circus.

1203
02:15:46.000 --> 02:15:50.583 line:82%
Sahir Khan, the owner of the circus,
is Iqbal Haroon Khan's son.

1204
02:15:51.667 --> 02:15:53.000 line:82%
A gentleman who 25 years ago...

1205
02:15:53.250 --> 02:15:56.000 line:82%
...took his life because of you
and your bank, Mr. Anderson.

1206
02:15:56.500 --> 02:15:57.542 line:82%
What's your point?

1207
02:15:58.000 --> 02:16:01.875 line:82%
My point isn't for you.
It's for the Chicago Police.

1208
02:16:02.375 --> 02:16:03.250 line:82%
What do you need?

1209
02:16:04.583 --> 02:16:08.417 line:82%
Cooperation. I'm bringing him in.
Tonight.

1210
02:16:14.292 --> 02:16:15.125 line:82%
You cheated.

1211
02:16:25.125 --> 02:16:26.458 line:82%
What is it?

1212
02:16:32.042 --> 02:16:34.083 line:82%
When you're in a crowd...

1213
02:16:34.708 --> 02:16:36.625 line:82%
...you're the only one I see.

1214
02:16:38.792 --> 02:16:40.750 line:82%
Now there's only you.

1215
02:16:41.292 --> 02:16:44.083 line:82%
And I don't know how
to look at you.

1216
02:16:45.125 --> 02:16:46.292 line:82%
Careful, boss.

1217
02:16:46.667 --> 02:16:49.833 line:82%
Talk like that and people will think
you're my boyfriend.

1218
02:16:50.458 --> 02:16:51.875 line:82%
Let them.

1219
02:16:54.083 --> 02:16:56.167 line:82%
So which one is my boyfriend?

1220
02:16:58.042 --> 02:16:59.250 line:82%
You really are two people.

1221
02:16:59.750 --> 02:17:00.833 line:82%
You know that, right?

1222
02:17:03.875 --> 02:17:05.708 line:82%
One is my boss.

1223
02:17:06.458 --> 02:17:09.917 line:82%
Nice, but has a big ego.

1224
02:17:11.208 --> 02:17:13.750 line:82%
He always ignores me.

1225
02:17:16.042 --> 02:17:17.292 line:82%
And there's you.

1226
02:17:17.958 --> 02:17:20.500 line:82%
When you look at me, I feel...

1227
02:17:22.042 --> 02:17:24.250 line:82%
...as though I'm the answer
to every question.

1228
02:17:26.042 --> 02:17:27.667 line:82%
Like I'm the rain.

1229
02:17:28.167 --> 02:17:30.583 line:82%
Falling only for you.

1230
02:17:33.417 --> 02:17:35.333 line:82%
You look at me...

1231
02:17:37.792 --> 02:17:39.458 line:82%
The way you're looking now.

1232
02:17:42.250 --> 02:17:43.250 line:82%
Tell me.

1233
02:17:44.292 --> 02:17:45.458 line:82%
Which me...

1234
02:17:46.750 --> 02:17:47.958 line:82%
...do you like?

1235
02:17:50.917 --> 02:17:52.875 line:82%
You're my affliction.

1236
02:17:54.458 --> 02:17:55.875 line:82%
You're my cure.

1237
02:17:58.042 --> 02:17:59.583 line:82%
You're my affliction.

1238
02:18:01.417 --> 02:18:02.292 line:82%
You're my cure.

1239
02:18:17.083 --> 02:18:18.125 line:82%
This one.

1240
02:18:48.875 --> 02:18:49.833 line:82%
Good evening, sir.

1241
02:18:50.083 --> 02:18:54.042 line:82%
Sorry, the park is closing in 5 minutes.
Hope you had a great day here.

1242
02:19:03.500 --> 02:19:05.000 line:82%
You're my best friend.

1243
02:19:05.958 --> 02:19:09.000 line:82%
All thanks to you, best friend.

1244
02:19:14.417 --> 02:19:16.417 line:82%
You think of me as a friend?

1245
02:19:18.167 --> 02:19:20.875 line:82%
Will you keep my secret?

1246
02:19:41.708 --> 02:19:43.833 line:82%
ACP Jai Dixit. Mumbai Police.

1247
02:19:46.125 --> 02:19:47.167 line:82%
Jai Dixit?

1248
02:19:47.583 --> 02:19:49.333 line:82%
I made friends for a reason.

1249
02:19:50.167 --> 02:19:52.208 line:82%
But I know the meaning
of friendship now.

1250
02:19:52.667 --> 02:19:54.500 line:82%
Friends don't use each other.

1251
02:19:56.708 --> 02:19:59.375 line:82%
Don't be scared. It was all a sham.

1252
02:20:00.250 --> 02:20:02.583 line:82%
The friendship wasn't.

1253
02:20:02.917 --> 02:20:04.500 line:82%
Friends don't lie.

1254
02:20:04.792 --> 02:20:06.583 line:82%
Samar, I'm here to help you.

1255
02:20:06.833 --> 02:20:08.125 line:82%
You lied to me.

1256
02:20:09.958 --> 02:20:15.667 line:82%
The bank wronged your father.
They've been punished enough.

1257
02:20:16.250 --> 02:20:18.792 line:82%
They've lost all face. Their shares
have plummeted.

1258
02:20:19.042 --> 02:20:20.083 line:82%
They're bust.

1259
02:20:20.417 --> 02:20:21.750 line:82%
But it's still around.

1260
02:20:22.208 --> 02:20:23.208 line:82%
Papa isn't.

1261
02:20:23.917 --> 02:20:26.375 line:82%
Forgiveness is better than revenge.

1262
02:20:27.125 --> 02:20:29.208 line:82%
You've had your revenge.

1263
02:20:29.667 --> 02:20:31.417 line:82%
Time to stop your fight.

1264
02:20:31.750 --> 02:20:33.917 line:82%
You lied to me.

1265
02:20:34.500 --> 02:20:36.750 line:82%
I know you and Sahir are twins.

1266
02:20:40.083 --> 02:20:43.125 line:82%
You're the secret of Sahir's
great circus.

1267
02:20:45.667 --> 02:20:48.458 line:82%
The police know you pulled off
the heists together.

1268
02:20:51.208 --> 02:20:54.042 line:82%
You know our secret? Not good.

1269
02:20:57.375 --> 02:20:58.625 line:82%
You're my friend.

1270
02:20:59.125 --> 02:21:00.667 line:82%
I'm here for you.

1271
02:21:01.000 --> 02:21:02.833 line:82%
But you must help me.

1272
02:21:03.375 --> 02:21:06.875 line:82%
Come with me. Give a statement
to the police. Turn yourself in.

1273
02:21:07.458 --> 02:21:08.375 line:82%
Trust me.

1274
02:21:08.708 --> 02:21:10.875 line:82%
I'll help you both in court.

1275
02:21:11.250 --> 02:21:13.167 line:82%
We'll make an leniency plea.

1276
02:21:13.500 --> 02:21:14.583 line:82%
No.

1277
02:21:14.917 --> 02:21:16.917 line:82%
Samar, you've no option.

1278
02:21:17.458 --> 02:21:20.000 line:82%
I'm asking you because Sahir
won't listen to me.

1279
02:21:20.375 --> 02:21:22.000 line:82%
He won't stop his mission.

1280
02:21:23.000 --> 02:21:25.625 line:82%
Do you know how this ends?
In death.

1281
02:21:27.958 --> 02:21:29.917 line:82%
Only you can save the situation.

1282
02:21:30.208 --> 02:21:33.333 line:82%
Save your brother. Save yourself.
And Aliya's love.

1283
02:21:35.542 --> 02:21:37.417 line:82%
Trust me. There's no way out.

1284
02:21:39.542 --> 02:21:42.500 line:82%
I'm your friend. Please trust me.

1285
02:22:16.375 --> 02:22:21.542 line:82%
You're like a bad cold
one can't shake.

1286
02:22:23.000 --> 02:22:24.500 line:82%
Sahir the Wizard.

1287
02:22:26.750 --> 02:22:29.792 line:82%
I'm a circus man. We don't
only fool the eye...

1288
02:22:30.417 --> 02:22:33.125 line:82%
...but death too. Every day.

1289
02:22:33.667 --> 02:22:35.583 line:82%
I like your trick.

1290
02:22:37.042 --> 02:22:38.458 line:82%
You're a real magician.

1291
02:22:39.708 --> 02:22:40.917 line:82%
Guile.

1292
02:22:42.000 --> 02:22:43.250 line:82%
Invention.

1293
02:22:43.917 --> 02:22:45.250 line:82%
And deception.

1294
02:22:45.833 --> 02:22:48.458 line:82%
Put them together and that's
magic for you.

1295
02:24:17.708 --> 02:24:21.208 line:82%
So a cop and thief can only
be enemies? Right, Mr.Dixit?

1296
02:24:21.708 --> 02:24:23.417 line:82%
Making a mistake.

1297
02:24:24.292 --> 02:24:25.750 line:82%
I can help you.

1298
02:24:29.417 --> 02:24:31.375 line:82%
It was never your fight, Jai.

1299
02:24:31.750 --> 02:24:34.083 line:82%
I gave you the chance to
go back to India.

1300
02:24:35.250 --> 02:24:36.500 line:82%
But you...

1301
02:24:37.417 --> 02:24:39.042 line:82%
...you conned us.

1302
02:24:40.500 --> 02:24:41.958 line:82%
Samar is innocent, weak.

1303
02:24:42.167 --> 02:24:44.042 line:82%
You're weak without him.

1304
02:24:48.792 --> 02:24:51.042 line:82%
You're right.

1305
02:24:53.500 --> 02:24:56.042 line:82%
But you weren't right by Samar.

1306
02:24:57.208 --> 02:24:59.000 line:82%
Played with his feelings.

1307
02:24:59.708 --> 02:25:01.125 line:82%
Used him.

1308
02:25:06.000 --> 02:25:08.583 line:82%
They say think good thoughts
before dying.

1309
02:25:09.458 --> 02:25:13.000 line:82%
So remember your few good deeds.

1310
02:25:17.667 --> 02:25:19.708 line:82%
I'd happily watch you die.

1311
02:25:20.208 --> 02:25:21.292 line:82%
But...

1312
02:25:22.000 --> 02:25:23.792 line:82%
I have a bank to wipe out.

1313
02:25:27.167 --> 02:25:28.208 line:82%
Enjoy the ride.

1314
02:25:47.792 --> 02:25:49.833 line:82%
It's all about timing, brother.

1315
02:26:16.542 --> 02:26:17.792 line:82%
22nd May.

1316
02:26:18.417 --> 02:26:22.042 line:82%
The most important and dangerous
day of our lives.

1317
02:26:29.833 --> 02:26:33.792 line:82%
The storm that shook our souls...

1318
02:26:34.625 --> 02:26:37.167 line:82%
...will smile and still itself.

1319
02:26:44.625 --> 02:26:48.750 line:82%
Today we wrap the bank in a shroud.

1320
02:26:50.125 --> 02:26:54.000 line:82%
Today the Western Bank of Chicago
gets buried.

1321
02:26:58.542 --> 02:27:01.667 line:82%
WESTERN BANK OF CHICAGO.

1322
02:27:15.667 --> 02:27:16.583 line:82%
Move!

1323
02:27:16.875 --> 02:27:18.792 line:82%
Take your positions.

1324
02:27:32.583 --> 02:27:33.167 line:82%
Go, go.

1325
02:28:03.583 --> 02:28:06.250 line:82%
Gas! Get everybody out.
Go!

1326
02:28:19.958 --> 02:28:20.833 line:82%
Come on.

1327
02:28:31.417 --> 02:28:32.583 line:82%
Come on. Go!

1328
02:28:35.250 --> 02:28:36.000 line:82%
Damn it!

1329
02:29:52.875 --> 02:29:53.833 line:82%
Samar, ready?

1330
02:29:54.292 --> 02:29:55.167 line:82%
Always.

1331
02:32:04.417 --> 02:32:07.708 line:82%
Thank you, Mummy.
Spotted us from heaven?

1332
02:32:08.667 --> 02:32:09.792 line:82%
Let's go.

1333
02:36:08.875 --> 02:36:11.375 line:82%
Never caught a thief by moonlight.

1334
02:36:15.083 --> 02:36:18.875 line:82%
If I wasn't a cop, I'd write a poem
right now.

1335
02:36:19.208 --> 02:36:22.042 line:82%
I can think of one. May I?

1336
02:36:25.833 --> 02:36:26.417 line:82%
Next time.

1337
02:37:08.625 --> 02:37:12.583 line:82%
Got a poem for this situation, too.
May I?

1338
02:37:15.625 --> 02:37:17.125 line:82%
Forget them!

1339
02:37:17.542 --> 02:37:19.542 line:82%
Can't catch them. Confirmed.

1340
02:37:21.250 --> 02:37:23.083 line:82%
The night belongs to thieves.

1341
02:37:24.000 --> 02:37:25.167 line:82%
Let him run.

1342
02:37:26.000 --> 02:37:27.125 line:82%
The morning belongs to us.

1343
02:37:27.500 --> 02:37:30.042 line:82%
How? He always has a new card
up his sleeve.

1344
02:37:30.458 --> 02:37:32.083 line:82%
But I hold an ace.

1345
02:37:35.417 --> 02:37:39.167 line:82%
I need choppers and a SWAT team
at sunrise.

1346
02:38:11.083 --> 02:38:11.750 line:82%
Samar.

1347
02:38:31.250 --> 02:38:33.583 line:82%
We'll find a way.

1348
02:38:34.167 --> 02:38:35.042 line:82%
Samar, let's go.

1349
02:38:37.375 --> 02:38:39.417 line:82%
She's crying.

1350
02:38:39.750 --> 02:38:41.292 line:82%
It's a set-up. Come.

1351
02:39:16.875 --> 02:39:17.792 line:82%
Sahir.

1352
02:39:19.833 --> 02:39:20.958 line:82%
It's over.

1353
02:40:13.458 --> 02:40:15.000 line:82%
Don't want to run any more, Jai.

1354
02:40:15.458 --> 02:40:17.542 line:82%
No place left to run.

1355
02:40:20.250 --> 02:40:22.042 line:82%
You can arrest me, but...

1356
02:40:22.625 --> 02:40:24.708 line:82%
...you've no proof to show in court.

1357
02:40:25.542 --> 02:40:27.000 line:82%
It'll take a lifetime to prove.

1358
02:40:28.000 --> 02:40:30.875 line:82%
Here's all the proof you need.

1359
02:40:31.375 --> 02:40:33.333 line:82%
How and when I pulled off the heists.

1360
02:40:33.833 --> 02:40:34.833 line:82%
Everything.

1361
02:40:35.583 --> 02:40:36.958 line:82%
Take me in.

1362
02:40:38.958 --> 02:40:40.167 line:82%
Let Samar go.

1363
02:40:40.667 --> 02:40:42.167 line:82%
The guilty must be punished.

1364
02:40:42.500 --> 02:40:43.833 line:82%
Not my brother.

1365
02:40:44.708 --> 02:40:45.667 line:82%
Not Samar.

1366
02:40:46.042 --> 02:40:47.542 line:82%
It was all me, Jai.

1367
02:40:47.917 --> 02:40:50.042 line:82%
All my planning. I did everything.

1368
02:40:50.875 --> 02:40:53.542 line:82%
You have the thief.
What more do you want?

1369
02:40:55.458 --> 02:40:58.750 line:82%
Samar is innocent...
let him go.

1370
02:41:02.667 --> 02:41:03.292 line:82%
Come on, Jai.

1371
02:41:03.625 --> 02:41:04.708 line:82%
It's a good deal.

1372
02:41:13.375 --> 02:41:14.292 line:82%
It's a deal.

1373
02:41:14.750 --> 02:41:15.708 line:82%
You promise?

1374
02:41:56.042 --> 02:41:58.708 line:82%
You don't need to pretend
you're Sahir anymore.

1375
02:42:01.542 --> 02:42:04.375 line:82%
You're not a shadow now.
You're Samar.

1376
02:42:07.250 --> 02:42:09.750 line:82%
You're not weak. You're Samar.

1377
02:42:12.250 --> 02:42:13.625 line:82%
Time for hiding is over.

1378
02:42:14.125 --> 02:42:16.792 line:82%
Time you live and dream.

1379
02:42:20.083 --> 02:42:21.583 line:82%
We were two.

1380
02:42:22.125 --> 02:42:23.250 line:82%
We lived as one.

1381
02:42:25.083 --> 02:42:28.417 line:82%
One will live now...
for us two.

1382
02:42:45.667 --> 02:42:47.167 line:82%
Where to?

1383
02:42:48.208 --> 02:42:49.000 line:82%
Let go!

1384
02:42:51.167 --> 02:42:53.083 line:82%
They can't touch you, Samar.

1385
02:42:53.583 --> 02:42:55.375 line:82%
It ends with me.

1386
02:42:55.708 --> 02:42:57.958 line:82%
You'll be with Aliya. Free.

1387
02:42:59.417 --> 02:43:00.833 line:82%
I won't let go.

1388
02:43:01.583 --> 02:43:02.542 line:82%
Let go, Samar.

1389
02:43:02.917 --> 02:43:05.375 line:82%
Papa said: "Never let go of his hand.

1390
02:43:05.667 --> 02:43:07.958 line:82%
"Never leave his side."

1391
02:43:08.417 --> 02:43:09.833 line:82%
Let go, brother.

1392
02:43:10.583 --> 02:43:11.833 line:82%
This world isn't for me.

1393
02:43:22.083 --> 02:43:23.792 line:82%
People of God are we.

1394
02:43:24.125 --> 02:43:26.458 line:82%
Who can defy us?

1395
02:43:30.875 --> 02:43:32.917 line:82%
People of God are we.

1396
02:43:33.875 --> 02:43:35.708 line:82%
Who can defy us?

1397
02:43:36.625 --> 02:43:39.708 line:82%
Basking under a thousand suns
of hope.

1398
02:43:40.292 --> 02:43:42.500 line:82%
With steely resolve.

1399
02:43:43.042 --> 02:43:44.583 line:82%
With fearless step.

1400
02:43:45.292 --> 02:43:47.167 line:82%
Today we set forth to write...

1401
02:43:47.583 --> 02:43:48.792 line:82%
...our destiny.

1402
02:44:06.167 --> 02:44:09.000 line:82%
High up in the sky.

1403
02:44:10.000 --> 02:44:12.458 line:82%
Is our world.

1404
02:44:13.833 --> 02:44:19.958 line:82%
In its shimmering folds
is our happiness.

1405
02:44:21.458 --> 02:44:25.792 line:82%
With the moon's mesh.

1406
02:44:29.042 --> 02:44:33.500 line:82%
We'll gather the stars.

1407
02:44:36.667 --> 02:44:40.958 line:82%
This place is a place of magic.

1408
02:44:44.250 --> 02:44:48.625 line:82%
Free of all sorrow.

1409
02:44:55.667 --> 02:44:58.292 line:82%
People of God are we.

1410
02:44:59.500 --> 02:45:02.000 line:82%
Who can defy us?

